# Beplus Fast Product Filter & Live Search for WooCommerce — core

- **Briefing:** Read [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md) first; architecture in [`Document Plugin.md`](../../Document Plugin.md).
- **Slug / i18n:** Text domain `beplus-fast-product-filter-live-search-for-woocommerce`; PHP hooks/functions `beplus_fast_product_filter_live_search_`; PSR-4 `BePlusFastProductFilterLiveSearch\` → `src/`.
- **Constants:** `BEPLUS_FAST_PRODUCT_FILTER_LIVE_SEARCH_VERSION`, `BEPLUS_FAST_PRODUCT_FILTER_LIVE_SEARCH_PLUGIN_DIR`, `BEPLUS_FAST_PRODUCT_FILTER_LIVE_SEARCH_PLUGIN_URL`, `BEPLUS_FAST_PRODUCT_FILTER_LIVE_SEARCH_PLUGIN_BASENAME`.
- **Architecture:** Single entry `Plugin::boot()`; modules extend `AbstractModule` and attach hooks only in `register()` — no side effects at file load.
- **After editing** `admin/js/**`, `assets/**`, or block sources under `blocks/**`, run **`npm run build`** or **`npm run start`** from the plugin root.
- **Do not treat as source** (regenerate via npm): `build/admin.js`, `build/admin.asset.php`, `build/frontend.js`, `build/blocks/**`.
- **Target:** WordPress 6.0+; PHP 7.4+ (prefer `declare(strict_types=1);` in new PHP under `src/`).
- **Architecture reference:** [`Document Plugin.md`](../../Document Plugin.md) § Core class map.

```text
❌ add_action() at top level in src/Search/SearchEngine.php
✅ Register hooks inside SearchRegistry::register() or the owning module

❌ Edit build/admin.js by hand to fix a bug
✅ Fix admin/js/** or blocks/** then npm run build
```
